I believe that the United States has a moral and economic imperative to mitigate the impacts of climate change. However, I do not think that H.J. Res. 109, the #GreenNewDeal is the right solution.

Read my statement to find out why. https://vandrew.house.gov/media/press-releases/congressman-jeff-van-drew-s-nj-02-statement-green-new-deal …

I believe that climate change is real, is driven mainly by human activity and that it is driving real-world changes such as extreme weather events, hotter temperatures, rising sea levels, and ocean acidification. #GreenNewDeal

I am very pleased with the benefits that this bipartisan funding agreement will have for South Jersey. Check out the details about the funding for the William J. Hughes @FAATechCenter and employee raises! #Bipartisanship #FundingAgreement #Budget2019 #SouthJersey @FAANews pic.twitter.com/D3JpnIFZ1v

Some of the critical investments in South Jersey from the agreement are:

- William J. Hughes Technical Center 
- Federal Aviation Administration (FAA)
- Unmanned Aircraft Systems (UAS) Research 
- U.S. Coast Guard (USCG)

#Bipartisanship #FAA #USCG #SouthJersey #Budget2019

While this deal isn't perfect, it reflects the needs of the American people, secures our borders & makes significant investments on the priorities of South Jersey. #Bipartisanship #FAA #USCG #SouthJersey #Budget2019
I am grateful that we have come to an agreement & the American people will not suffer through another shutdown. #Bipartisanship #FAA #USCG #SouthJersey #Budget2019

Today, I voted on a compromise bill to fund the federal government for the remainder of the fiscal year and invest in South Jersey. The funding package now goes to President Trump where it awaits his signature. #FAA #USCG #SouthJersey #Budget2019 https://vandrew.house.gov/media/press-releases/rep-van-drew-votes-compromise-bill-fund-government-and-prevent-another …

South Jersey's local economy is dependent on fishing, tourism and wildlife watching – the bottom line is offshore oil and gas drilling isn’t worth the risk. -JVD #ProtectOurCoast #NoSeismic #ACEPA #BlocktheBlast #SouthJersey @oceana

Today, the majority of my New Jersey colleagues and I came together to express our concern with the continued closure of the Atlantic City Rail Line. @NJTRANSIT's failure to meet its own deadlines and lack of transparency is unacceptable. #ACRailLine #AtlanticCity #NJPols pic.twitter.com/OhHKtSs6fq
That’s why a majority of my New Jersey colleagues and I are sending a letter of admonishment to @NJTRANSIT. #NJTransit #atlanticcity #SouthJersey #ACRailLine

I will continue to put pressure on @NJTRANSIT, to tell the truth to the people of #SouthJersey about and fix the #ACRailLine. I won't stop until we get resolution on this issue. #NJTransit #atlanticcity
I have repeatedly tried to get answers from the Executive Director of @NJTRANSIT but have been continuously stonewalled. #NJTransit #atlanticcity #ACRailLine #SouthJersey

On Thursday I addressed the House floor to put pressure on @NJTRANSIT, to tell the truth to the people of South Jersey about the AC Rail Line after they promised it would be finished by early 2019, but recently announced it would take up to 5 more months. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rnzNJlLHT7k&feature=youtu.be …
